<h2>Authentication changes in ITOM Marketplace</h2><div>During February 2019, Software&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt; background-color: transparent;">Passport user accounts were migrated to Access
Manager as part of the separation from HPE.&nbsp; However, ITOM Marketplace
APIs such as the ones used in HCM/CSA Content Store were not able to make this
migration and have continued to use Software Passport Credentials to
authenticate.&nbsp;ITOM Marketplace Team announced the end of authentication using Software Passport by August&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: transparent;">30th</span><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">2019.&nbsp; This means, HCM/CSA Conent Store will no longer be able to authenticate to ITOM Marketplace using the Software Passport Credentials starting September 1st 2019.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 1.1px; text-transform: initial; background-color: transparent;"><br></span></div><h2>Actions Required</h2><div><p style="margin: 7.5pt 0in 0.0001pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span style="font-size:9.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,sans-serif;color:#333333">To update your credentials to
Access Manager in Content Store, first create an&nbsp;<a href="https://www.microfocus.com/selfreg/jsp/createAccount.jsp"><span style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175);">Access Manager
account here</span></a>&nbsp;if you do not have one. If you access entitled
software, you should also configure your entitlements and contracts in
the&nbsp;<a href="https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/group/softwaresupport/settings?lang=en&amp;cc=us&amp;hpappid=206728_SSO_PRO"><span style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175);">My entitlements
section here</span></a>&nbsp;in MySupport.&nbsp; You can go to the&nbsp;<a href="https://marketplace.microfocus.com/login?returnUrl=/itom"><span style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175);">Marketplace
login page here</span></a>&nbsp;and login using Access Manager to test your
account if needed.<o:p></o:p></span></p><h2 style="margin-top: 22.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">HCM/CSA Content Store Configuration Steps</h2></div><div><p style="margin: 7.5pt 0in 0.0001pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span style="font-size:9.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,sans-serif;color:#333333">To update Content Store
settings in HCM/CSA:</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 21pt; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:
